- "Triple crown" in this context refers to the top ranking in motor voltage, motor amps, and GPM;
- "Champions" refers to the pumps that have the highest values in all three metrics;
- "Flow rate" is measured in US gallons per minute (GPM).

- "Due for maintenance" refers to pumps whose next maintenance date is before the current date;
- "Most recent performance records" are the latest records based on the timestamp;
- "Flow rate" is measured in gallons per minute (GPM).

- Total dynamic head (TDH) is a measure of the total pressure head in a pump system, including static head, friction head, and velocity head.;
- Active solar arrays are those with an operational status marked as 'active'.;
- The query calculates the average TDH across all active solar arrays, giving a sense of the typical performance of pumps in these arrays.

- 'recently maintained' refers to the most recent maintenance date recorded in the `maintenance_records` table;
- 'average efficiency' is calculated by averaging the efficiency percentages of the same pump model;
- 'overall average efficiency' is the average efficiency of all pumps across all models.

- "shining stars" refers to pumps with above-average efficiency;
- "outshine the average" means having an efficiency greater than the average efficiency of all pumps;
- "latest performance" refers to the most recent entry in the performance log;
- "solar array details" include the number of panels, orientation, and installation date.

- Ambient temperature between 15 and 25 degrees is considered optimal for pump performance;
- Motor power consumption greater than 400 watts indicates a high-performance pump;
- Average efficiency greater than 10% is a threshold for good performance.

- "Good working condition" refers to pumps that are not 'out_of_order' or 'under_maintenance';
- "Well-maintained" refers to pumps that have had more than 2 maintenance records;
- "Consistently perform above average" refers to pumps with an average efficiency greater than 80%, average US GPM greater than 50, average PSI greater than 20, and average TDH in feet greater than 10.

- "Maintenance mode" indicates that the pump is not currently operational and is under repair or inspection;
- "Open alerts" refer to unresolved issues that have been flagged in the system;
- "Reduced power output" is an alert description indicating that the pump is not performing at its expected capacity;
- "PSI" stands for pounds per square inch, a measure of pressure that can indicate the pump's performance.

- 'heart of each pump' refers to the motor, which is a critical component of the pump;
- 'peak electrical strength' refers to the maximum motor voltage;
- 'operates with more than half its potential' means the efficiency is greater than 50%;
- 'voltage surpassing the threshold of 200' means the motor voltage is greater than 200.
